The paper deals with the maximum traveling salesman problem, which is a classic problem in combinatorial optimization. The algorithm presented in the paper is deterministic and combinatorial, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem also involves finding an optimal tour through a set of points, which suggests that it may be related to computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the use of approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as well.
